That line is just heartbreakingingly lovely.&nbsp; 

Rented The Apartment with Jack&nbsp;Lemmon and Shirley Maclaine. I&nbsp;cant tell you how pleasing it is to watch a truly good movie that came from ages ago, and yet still makes sense, as if time were just adjusting to fit us, and not vice versa. I suppose I'm talking about the nature of cinema,&nbsp; but also the way we communicate our feelings and attitudes when it comes to love self identity;&nbsp; in the movie they are the same as reflected in today's modern films (the GOOD ones).&nbsp;&nbsp; Is it wrong to find that comforting? Maybe if I&nbsp;were watching Roger Moore in Octopussy, but I&nbsp;dont think so in this case. Not in this movie. And who does Jack Lemmon remind me of? I&nbsp;know Kevin&nbsp;Spacey always said Lemmon was his hero, but alas poor Kevin hasnt been around in ages. No, maybe a mixture of Jim&nbsp;Carrey from Eternal Sunshine and George Clooney in One Fine Day. (the latter really is an underrated film.)&nbsp;

Ok, back to my midnight movie treat.

&nbsp;DC sleeps alone tonight.&nbsp; 

So much has happened in this past year. Lots of people migrating north, some south. Its sad, but also really amazing to watch people transform and make these leaps-- its inspiring&nbsp;i guess is what i intend to say.&nbsp; 

I had told my District manager last week&nbsp;that I'm quitting my job sometime by the end of this summer and going back home. Its been stewing in my brain for a while now. The damn broke a couple weeks ago, quite literally in the back office when I was speaking with my sweet sweet completely opposite-of-what-i-thought-he-was&nbsp;DM (dungeon master josh)&nbsp;and he basically said, really unexpectedly, "i want whats best for you, take whatever time you need to step back and think about what you want to do, dont stress, and I'm here for you. " Wow. Nice guy.&nbsp; 

So this month shall be the month of great contemplation and yes&nbsp;decision-making. I know I've got to come up with something, and quick. I cant help but be affected by the choices other people in my life make, lots of them are deciding on grad school, pursuing a lifelong dream, or just basically moving forward with their respective&nbsp;lives. I cant be impulsive but I've had my heart set on several things, it just takes such tough skin and perseverence. I know its all fear-based. (Cheesy song, "I dare you to move, I dare you to lift yourself up off the ground" plays consistently in my head)&nbsp; 

Sigh. There were alot of reasons why I originally came to DC. I feel like its getting old now, its wearing on me. Sometimes its because of "him", because he was the last reason why i said, "ok, so I'll stay." And now I am all out of reasons other than the pragmatic logical ones like, "cant quit a job until you get a new one...what about your health benefits katherine?...." blah blah. So I've re-vamped my resume, my dad's helping me out, I'm looking into some grad school programs. And, well, We'll see.&nbsp; 
Yes we'll see how the great inter-connected Jungian synchronicity principle works this time. On me, on my family, on friends . We'll see. 


And Josh, when or if you read this--&nbsp;thank you. Just ya know, for&nbsp;just being the best big brother a girl&nbsp;could have. Sometime I hope you'll write a journal entry here about your innermost thoughts, or at least some of them, because the ones that you share with me are so much more frickin' interesting than anything I could write about.

back&nbsp; in Arlington.&nbsp;
on the brink of part-time job, on the brink of-on the brink of full time real job.&nbsp;

woman of few words these days. all action, i swears it.

So my friend of friend's liver status has improved, but her kidney's aren't doing well. she has to do dialysis everyday. I'm trying to get ahold of Matt and Patty but they dont seem to want anyone else involved, so I;m just gonna let it be, in the words of Paul McCartney (unless you're a Happiness is a Warm Gun type person then you probably think Lennon wrote most of the Beatles licks)&nbsp;
Anywho, so. My life. Your life. Our lives, intertwining together in this place we call livejournal. How intriguing to me.&nbsp;

Today on the metro ride home, some kid offered his brother a trip to Catalina over the phone. I guess he had a free ticket, his semester was over and decided he wanted to lay low. He was wearing a baseball cap and corduroy jacket, and kept his head down the entire ride. I imagined in my state of fantasy/voyeurism that he's a character out of that show Dirty Sexy Money, though I've yet to see it. (was it cut?) The guy next to him was playing with an arubix cube and I was praying he'd get it right before we arrived at my stop; he came very close, but no cigar.&nbsp;

Hmm, what else? I'm one music theory, one Jesus paper, one Comparative politics test away from graduating. How completely terrifying! I went to the career center and was bombarded with disillusionment. Not really, I'm excited to revise my resume actually. The "career consultant" gave me this sheet of verbs to use. So if I were to say I spent an entire summer chatting with the guy next to me in the Purchasing department, what I really did was mediated/coached/ or maybe resolved some of the daily problems that arose in context to um, purchasing orders or some such nonsense, Ehhh,I wouldnt actually say that, I'm tired. Ok, maybe I will. We'll see. HA.&nbsp;

Goodnight everyone. Good afternoon? to one.&nbsp; :)

yeah so&nbsp;last night rocked. or, peanut butter cups + popcorn+ penne pasta+ wash it all down with some pinot grigio rocked&nbsp;while I watched season 1 Arrested Development again. I've now unintentionally memorized every line from that season.....High fastening pants?&nbsp;

To clarify, I am half-way done with finals and it was really nice to relax by myself and basically crash. or, it was really necessary.&nbsp;

I've got ten days left to write two papers and study for a final. I think the mission can be completed.

So , heres a story, thats at the least entertaining to me. Today, in a moment of bravery I decided to post a post-it note with my number on the car of a guy I've been chatting with (scoping out) for the past few weeks. I always knew he drove the blue car that made a special sound when he pressed the unlock button. After I did it I felt very good, and off I went to the bus. When I get back the note is sadly still stuck on the window. Fast forward to nighttime--I go for a cigarette but this time decide to sit near the laundry steps so my landlord doesnt see me and ponder all the ways to throw me out of her kingdom because I'm technically loitering (according to the contract) even though nothing ever gets fixed and no one ever really gets in trouble 'round these parts. (even the people who decide to steal laundry detergent or break into a string of cars and steal GPS systems etc) Anyway, I'm sitting on the steps when out walks this giggly girl who is immediately followed by none other than the annointed messiah of my currently non-existant love life. I'm shocked. Shocked. Shocked. (YOU MUST LOVE ME, SINGS&nbsp;MADONNA AS EVITA)&nbsp;I say hello, he says hello, asks me how I am, blah blah blah (crying inside). He continues walking up the steps, out of my life, and into the WRONG FUCKING CAR. I mean, it made the special sound, but NOT the car I put the post-it note on. I feel like an idiot and immediately run to the other car and rip the note off in a fit of sadness/rage where it leaves an awful mark that even my nails can't remove. Two hours later I go outside again and run into my next door neighbor Evan, whose been consistantly&nbsp;asking me out&nbsp;on dates since the first day I met him. (I'm not tooting my own horn its just a fact and he's very sweet but not my type and he'll find someone nice and sweet and of the appropriate height because to be honest I like guys who are at least three inches taller than me--ok Josh, so There IS one preqreq I have for dating) He tells me that his dog died. The worst news in the world, right? I love my dogs my heart will break when they pass on. So I give him my condolenses, tell him he has nice dimples (shouldnt have done that but thought to throw him a bone no pun intended) and then as he walks onward guess which car he gets into--FUCKING POST-IT NOTE CAR!&nbsp; I dont know if he ever saw it. Maybe not. Maybe he did. Maybe thats why he asked me if I had brought a guy home the other night because the note clearly addresses someone other than him.&nbsp;

I feel really bad and I hope he didnt see the note + i want to crush that little ditz "annointed messiah" took out on a date in his non-post-it note car. Waaaah.&nbsp;

So in conclusion, see what happens when Sara sprains her ankle? The whole world is thrown off tilt! Nah, but I do hope you're ok!

Pardon me for my blasphemous language but I was just reamed another asshole by my tutor for being&nbsp;ten minutes late. The thing is, there really is no excuse other than just not being a morning person. Though&nbsp;I am usually pretty prompt and on time regardless of what part of the day, it must be the season change. Its completely got me out of whack. Ouch. I hurted.&nbsp; 

So, now that I am on campus and dont have class until 4, I think I'll be studious and go research More's vision of Utopia and read the rest of The Tempest. Shakespeare always make me feel better after I've been verbally abused by someone I havent even met yet.&nbsp; 

KKKKARMAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA.&nbsp; 

I'm out. Have a nice day people.&nbsp; 

::whoosh:: 

(sound of me disappearing)&nbsp;


ps--can you say reamed another asshole? or is it, reamed up the asshole? Josh keeps correcting me on my mixing of metaphors and whatnot. not even sure i spelled the word right.

as Adrienne Rich says.&nbsp;

I'm driving (not diving) the huge mother of a car to Crystal city. I'm excited. Going to Target with my friend Gabby to buy a desk which we shall assemble&nbsp;somewhat poorly&nbsp;but still call our own victory even after Jared comes over and "fixes" it.&nbsp;

Thanksgiving was fun. I was the designated driver for all my brothers friends. That was entertaining, too, actually.&nbsp;

And finally, once I get this video installation thing working I'm going to post some home made videos, if just to make me feel cool and avoid studying for finals and looking for a job. (Be afraid Josh...nah, just kidding.)&nbsp;


-kath
